# BraTS – Brain Tumor Segmentation Dataset

## 📌 Dataset Overview

- **Full Name:** Brain Tumor Segmentation (BraTS) Challenge Dataset  
- **Organizer:** MICCAI BraTS Challenge  
- **Official Website:** https://braintumorsegmentation.org/  
- **Primary Domain:** Glioma Brain MRI  
- **Access Type:** Public (Registration Required)  
- **Data Format:** NIfTI (.nii / .nii.gz)  
- **Imaging Type:** Multimodal Structural MRI  

---

## 🧠 Description

The BraTS dataset is a multi-institutional collection of pre-operative MRI scans of glioma patients. It is one of the most widely used benchmark datasets for automated brain tumor segmentation.

BraTS provides standardized, co-registered, skull-stripped, and intensity-normalized MRI volumes along with expert-annotated tumor segmentation masks. It serves as the official dataset for the MICCAI Brain Tumor Segmentation Challenge.

The dataset supports reproducible evaluation and comparison of segmentation algorithms across institutions.

---

## 📡 MRI Modalities Included

Each patient case contains four aligned MRI sequences:

| Modality | Description |
|----------|------------|
| T1 | Native T1-weighted anatomical MRI |
| T1c | T1-weighted MRI with gadolinium contrast |
| T2 | T2-weighted MRI (sensitive to fluid content) |
| FLAIR | Fluid Attenuated Inversion Recovery (highlights edema) |

All volumes are:
- Co-registered to a common anatomical template  
- Resampled to 1mm³ isotropic resolution  
- Skull-stripped  

---

## 🧩 Segmentation Labels

Ground-truth tumor annotations are provided with the following labels:

| Label Value | Tumor Region |
|------------|-------------|
| 0 | Background |
| 1 | Necrotic and Non-Enhancing Tumor Core |
| 2 | Peritumoral Edema |
| 4 | Enhancing Tumor |

### Derived Evaluation Regions

- **Whole Tumor (WT)** = 1 + 2 + 4  
- **Tumor Core (TC)** = 1 + 4  
- **Enhancing Tumor (ET)** = 4  

